5|$|On 5 November, the 2nd Marine Regiment {{launched}} Operation Steel Curtain {{against the}} border town of Husaybah. The Marines reported that ten Marines and 139 insurgents {{died in the}} offensive. Medical workers in Husaybah claimed that 97 civilians were killed. On 1 December, ten Marines from 2nd Battalion 7th Marines were killed by a massive IED while on a foot patrol <b>in</b> <b>Fallujah.</b>|$|E
